-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 12:53AM EDT
-- None



July 31 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* AMC Networks Inc <AMCX.O>, a U.S. media company that owns cable channels, is in talks to buy a stake in BBC America, BBC Worldwide's U.S. channel, a source familiar with the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL4N0Q576U]  * European private equity firm Charterhouse [CHCAP.UL] is readying the sale of UK skincare company Deb Group this year in a deal worth about 500 million pounds ($845 million) including debt, four sources with knowledge of the talks said on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0Q55JP]  * Troubled life insurer and annuity provider The Phoenix Companies Inc <PNX.N> has hired investment banks Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> and Sandler O'Neill and Partners to explore a sale, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0Q524H]  * Germany's ZF Friedrichshafen AG is in advanced talks to acquire U.S.-based TRW Automotive Holdings Corp <TRW.N> for nearly $12 billion, in a deal that would create an automotive supply powerhouse, people familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL2N0Q5191]  * Italy's UniCredit SpA <CRDI.MI> will receive three binding offers on Wednesday to buy up to 50 percent of its asset management unit Pioneer, two sources close to the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL6N0Q532S]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]